TY  - JOUR
T1  - Discrete Lotsizing and Scheduling by Batch Sequencing
AU  - Jordan, Carsten
AU  - Drexl, Andreas
Y1  - 1998/05/01
PY  - 1998
DA  - 1998/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.44.5.698
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.44.5.698
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 698
EP  - 713
VL  - 44
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The discrete lotsizing and scheduling problem for one machine with sequence-dependent setup times and setup costs is solved as a single machine scheduling problem, which we term the batch sequencing problem. The relationship between the lotsizing problem and the batch sequencing problem is analyzed. The batch sequencing problem is solved with a branch & bound algorithm which is accelerated by bounding and dominance rules. The algorithm is compared with recently published procedures for solving variants of the DLSP and is found to be more efficient if the number of items is not large.
AB  - The discrete lotsizing and scheduling problem for one machine with sequence-dependent setup times and setup costs is solved as a single machine scheduling problem, which we term the batch sequencing problem. The relationship between the lotsizing problem and the batch sequencing problem is analyzed. The batch sequencing problem is solved with a branch & bound algorithm which is accelerated by bounding and dominance rules. The algorithm is compared with recently published procedures for solving variants of the DLSP and is found to be more efficient if the number of items is not large.
